                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100036">Italy</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100021">Florence</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1457">15th century, second half. </origDate>The calendar mentions the feast of the Transfiguration of Christ (<locus from="8r" to="8r" scheme="folios"/>), which was instituted in <date when="1457"/> and provides a terminus post quem for the manuscript. The place of origin is based on the coat of arms on <locus from="13r" to="13r" scheme="folios"/>, which is believed to be that of the Florence-based Corsini family. Furthermore, saint Zenobius of Florence is listed in the calender and litany (<locus from="5v" to="5v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="121v" to="121v" scheme="folios"/>).</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. At some point during the late 19th/early 20th century the manuscript was acquired by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102522">Per Hierta</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
