                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brwon and black ink, rubrics in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>All the major texts are opened by an historated intial over 5 lines. The initials are painted either in pink or blue, with details in blue, pink, green and gold, with additional details in purple and white. The initials are placed on a gold background. The initials are surrounded by a full border consisting of flowers and leaves inhabited by putti, animals and vases. The borders are painted in the same colours scheme as the initial. The historiated motifs are painted in skintones, then mainly in gold, blue and pink. The frame of the first initial also features a coat of arms surrounded by two angels (See Origin). The motifs are: <locus from="13r" to="13r" scheme="folios"/>: Madonna and Child (Hours of the Virgin); <locus from="104r" to="104r" scheme="folios"/>: David with lyre (Seven penitential psalms); <locus from="133r" to="133r" scheme="folios"/>: Man of Sorrows (Major hours of the Holy Cross); <locus from="166r" to="166r" scheme="folios"/>:
                                        Death/Skeleton (Office for the dead); <locus from="229r" to="229r" scheme="folios"/>: Christ Carrying the Cross (Minor hours of the Holy Cross); <locus from="38r" to="94r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="143r" to="162r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="230bis" to="233v" scheme="other"/>: Foliate chapter initials over 5 lines. These initials have the same shape and use the same colour scheme as the historiated initials. They are mainly used to introduce the hours. <locus from="1r" to="234r" scheme="folios"/>: Plain initials alternating in gold and blue over 1-2 lines with flourishing in red or blue. The flourishing often extends to frame the entire outer margin.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
